- ✅ `GET /api/{{routeName}}` → returns `200` and an array
- ✅ `GET /api/{{routeName}}/:id` → returns `200` for existing / `404` for missing
- ✅ `PUT /api/{{routeName}}/:id` → returns `200` for existing / `404` for missing
- ✅ `DELETE /api/{{routeName}}/:id` → returns `204` and removes the item / `404` for missing

**Service Tests** (`__tests__/services/{{routeName}}.service.test.js`):
- ✅ `create()` → generates unique id, stores all fields
- ✅ `findAll()` → returns empty array / all items
- ✅ `findOne(id)` → returns item / `undefined` for unknown id
- ✅ `update(id, payload)` → merges payload, returns updated item / `null` for unknown id
- ✅ `remove(id)` → removes item, returns `true` / `false` for unknown id

**Contextual Tests** (`contextual-tests/{{routeName}}.contextual.test.js`):
